This is a personal learning vault for a robotics engineer pursuing a PhD or Research Engineer or Research Scientist positions in industry.

Context:
- Robotics engineer at Meta Reality Labs working on tactile sensing, slip detection, and end-effector benchmarking.
- Applying to robotics PhD programs with research interests in contact-rich manipulation, tactile-conditioned policies, and cross-modal sensor inference.
- Already fluent in Python, C++, embedded systems, ROS 2, and real-time control.

Vault conventions:
- Numbered folders sort the knowledge: 00-inbox, 10-daily, 20-concepts, 30-papers, 40-projects, 50-courses, 90-archive.
- Notes use wikilinks liberally: [[Concept name]].
- Frontmatter uses YAML with a type field (daily, paper, concept, project).
- Math is written in LaTeX between $...$ for inline and $$...$$ for display.

When editing notes:
- Keep prose concise and technical.
- Add backlinks where connections exist.
- Preserve frontmatter.
- When implementing papers, place code in code/ subfolder with a clear README linking back to the relevant paper note.